{"type":"message","id":"9b78df13","parentId":"905e252f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:59:42.787Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, I've read the files:\n\n1. SOUL.md - I don't have a specific persona yet (no name, emoji, etc. defined - just general guidance)\n2. USER.md - Empty, don't know my human yet\n3. memory files - don't exist yet\n4. MEMORY.md - has Aliyun API key for image generation\n\nI need to greet the user. Based on SOUL.md, I should:\n- Be genuinely helpful, not performative\n- Skip \"Great question!\" filler\n- Be concise but thorough\n- Not be a corporate drone\n\nThe user wants me to greet them in my configured persona. But I don't have a defined persona yet (IDENTITY.md probably doesn't exist or is empty). Let me check - actually they said \"if one is provided\" so if there's no persona, I just greet them normally.\n\nSince there's no memory yet and USER.md is empty, this seems like a fresh start. I should be friendly but not over-the-top, and ask what they want to do.\n\nThe runtime model is kimi-coding/k2p5 which matches the default_model, so I don't need to mention that.\n\nLet me craft a simple greeting that's helpful without being too formal.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Hey. I'm online — looks like a fresh start, no memory yet. What are we working on tonight?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":1260,"output":271,"cacheRead":8704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10235,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773932373918}}
